==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Elephantiasis
<hw>El`e*phan*ti"a*sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.,
fr. Gr. <?/, from <grk>'ele`fas</grk>, <grk>'ele`fantos</grk>, an
elephant.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A disease of the skin, in which
it become enormously thickened, and is rough, hard, and fissured, like
an elephant's hide.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Elephantidae</ent>⟦br⟧
